# Launcher UI philosophy

MosAIq is a desktop search engine, not a chatbot. AI is integrated into search, not a separate chat pane.

## Ship-quality from day one

Do **not** build placeholder UI that will be thrown away. Every component should be designed as if it will ship in v1.0, even if functionality is incomplete. Layout, spacing, and styling evolve — structure stays stable.

## Product metaphor

- **Idle:** Subtle mosaic — every tile hints at a file; dormant data waiting to be explored.
- **Searching:** Mosaic fades; results take focus (Raycast / Spotlight workflow).
- **Opening a file:** One tile becomes the focus.

The mosaic is brand / idle state, **not** the default workflow chrome.

## Visual identity

Dark theme first. Tokens live in `frontend/src/theme.js` — do not scatter hex values.

Brand palette (identity guide):

| Role | Value |
|------|-------|
| Background | `#0D1117` |
| Accent teal | `#00E5A8` |
| Accent green | `#22C55E` |
| Cyan | `#06B6D4` |
| Blue | `#2563EB` |
| Neutral | `#8CA3A0` |

Brand mark: mosaic **M** with semantic network (`frontend/public/app-mark.png`, `favicon.svg`, `resources/icon.ico`). Use `AppMark` in UI. Product **name / company / version** live in root `app.config.json` — never hardcode the display name in components.

Feel: PowerToys Run + Raycast + Spotlight + Linear + Arc — minimal, keyboard-first, calm, premium, information-dense without clutter. Accents are teal→cyan→blue (AI-native), not flat single-green.

Avoid: ChatGPT clone layouts, card-heavy dashboards, loud neon everywhere, excessive animation, floating widgets, rainbow demo mosaics, fake result content.

## Component hierarchy (keep stable)

```
LauncherWindow
  SearchBar          — primary interaction; auto-focused; extensible for filename / semantic / AI / commands
  MosaicCanvas       — idle brand; exists permanently; fades when query non-empty
  Results / Empty    — slot for list → preview → AI summary → related → actions (add later, don't redesign)
  Footer / StatusBar — live status + shortcut hints (placeholders OK until wired)
```

## Design rules

- Reusable components; theme tokens / shared constants only
- Keyboard-first; dark mode first; responsive
- Empty state is intentional copy, not "No Results"
- Out of scope until their issues: search logic, indexing, AI, real results, full keyboard nav, preview, settings
